    <note>Xu(4) Ji(2) [780] His ancestors lived in Raozhou, Yugan xian. His great great grandfather, Xu(4) X [3385], moved to Xinzhou, Guiqi xian. Zhao(1) Bian's [375] grandson-in-law. His family was multigenerational affinal kin (shiyin) with Wang(1) Zao's [11625] family, which is documented by both men's relation with Zhao(1) Bian's lineage. According to Wang(1) Zao, Ji(2) earned the jinshi before he was capped, which probably means in the 1073 sitting. A Ji is listed in Jiangxi TZ, 21.13a as earning the jinshi in 1038, which is not possible although a feasible date for Ji's father, Zongju [24284], who earned the jinshi, but whose name also does not appear in the Jiangxi TZ. I am assuming that Zongju was the 1138 jinshi. XCB, 504.1a; SHY:ZG, 42.34b, 43.6b-7b, 68.22a; SHY:SH, 56.33a, 33b; Wang Zao, WJ, 26.4b-9b. CBD, 3, 2163-4.</note>
